{"id":1056,"date":"2016-04-11T23:37:05","date_gmt":"2016-04-12T04:37:05","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.HeyThatsMyHummus.com\/?p=1056"},"modified":"2016-04-11T23:37:05","modified_gmt":"2016-04-12T04:37:05","slug":"84-bend-it-like-bathrooms","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.HeyThatsMyHummus.com\/2016\/04\/84-bend-it-like-bathrooms\/","title":{"rendered":"[84] Bend It Like&#8230; Bathrooms?"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><em>Ripped from the headlines!<\/em><\/p>\n<p>We discuss two recent news stories that have had some traction lately&#8230;<\/p>\n<p>First, a Muslim seventh grade student from Houston was singled out in his class and told that <a href=\"http:\/\/www.khou.com\/news\/family-upset-after-teacher-allegedly-calls-student-a-terrorist\/114641445\" target=\"_blank\">&#8220;we all think you&#8217;re a terrorist&#8221;<\/a> when he laughed at a movie (Bend It Like Beckham) they had been watching. The teacher defended her actions saying that she was trying to teach the class about negative stereotypes. The student&#8217;s parents want the teacher removed. We discuss our experiences with being singled out due to stereotypes &#8212; and what we should be doing to ensure that this is not a common occurrence.<\/p>\n<p>And then we talk about the recent passage of &#8220;bathroom bills&#8221; which have popped up in the south (including <a href=\"http:\/\/www.charlotteobserver.com\/news\/politics-government\/article68401147.html\" target=\"_blank\">North Carolina&#8217;s HB2<\/a>) which adversely affect the trans community and mandate that people (including students) use restrooms consistent with the sex on their birth certificate &#8212; even if that does not match their gender identity.  What&#8217;s behind the fear-mongering?  And how do our own religious and cultural traditions deal with transgender identity?<\/p>\n<p>Let us know what you think on <a href=\"http:\/\/www.facebook.com\/HeyThatsMyHummus\" target=\"_blank\">Facebook<\/a> or <a href=